Identify and Remove Outliers Using Mean and Std Deviation Method¶

In [5]:
# Calculate mean and standard deviation
mean_price = df['price_per_sqft'].mean()
std_price = df['price_per_sqft'].std()
print("Mean =",mean_price)
print("Standard deviation =",std_price)

# Define a threshold (e.g., 3 standard deviations)
threshold = 3 * std_price

# Identify outliers
outliers_mean_std = df[(df['price_per_sqft'] > (mean_price + threshold)) | (df['price_per_sqft'] < (mean_price - threshold))]
print("\nOutliers founded by mean and std deviation method")
outliers_mean_std

Standard deviation = 106727.16032810867

IQR method¶

In [30]:
# Calculate IQR
Q1 = df['price_per_sqft'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['price_per_sqft'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
print("Q1 =",Q1)
print("Q3 =",Q3)

# Identify outliers
outliers_iqr = df[(df['price_per_sqft'] < (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) | (df['price_per_sqft'] > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))]
print("\nOutliers found by IQR Method")
outliers_iqr

Q1 = 4267.0
Q3 = 7317.0

z_score method¶

In [35]:
# Calculate Z scores
df['z_score'] = (df['price_per_sqft'] - mean_price) / std_price

# Define a Z score threshold 
z_threshold = 3

# Identify outliers
outliers_z_score = df[abs(df['z_score']) > z_threshold]
print("\n Outliers found by Z score Method")
outliers_z_score
